cs.ET, cs.AR, cs.DC, cs.EM, cs.SY

The paper deals with statistical static timing analysis, which is a topic related to electronic design automation (EDA) and circuit optimization. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.ET (Emerging Technologies), which includes papers on EDA, hardware design, and computer-aided design (CAD). 

The paper also discusses timing model generation and hierarchical timing analysis, which are topics related to computer architecture and digital circuits. Therefore, cs.AR (Architecture) and cs.DC (Digital Circuits) are also likely categories. 

The paper mentions the impact of variations in manufacturing processes, which is a topic related to electromagnetics and signal processing. Therefore, cs.EM (Electromagnetics) is another possible category. 

Finally, the paper proposes a method for improving timing accuracy by incorporating the correlation between modules, which is a topic related to control systems and automation. Therefore, cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category.
